# Call-Driven Tuning Loop

## Finish line

Every call automatically becomes a scored receipt (objective latency + LLM-judge
quality + failure taxonomy); a daily retro distills receipts into tunings —
allowlisted text changes auto-applied with receipts, everything else proposed as
reviewable diffs; and the loop has proven itself by shipping tunings that
measurably moved the numbers (fast-model A/B is the proving experiment). Done
when calls-in → tunings-out runs with neither Joel nor a steering session
driving it.

## Notes

- Chartered 2026-07-13 from Joel: "we had a good number of calls, let's use
  them to improve." Corpus at charter: 15 public / 3 private / 3 guest Convex
  sessions, 26 transcripts, 7 caller cards, per-turn latency rows.
- **Judge runs on Inngest leveraging pi agents** (Joel, 2026-07-13) — the
  agent-dispatch pattern; no new paid keys in system-bus.
- **Retro rides the 6am daily pipeline** (Joel, 2026-07-13) — same rhythm as
  the Bugle and the public-brain gardener.
- **Autonomy: gardener-style direct** (Joel, 2026-07-13) — low-risk text
  tunings auto-apply with receipts; code/config always gated. The allowlist is
  its own question.
- **Execution authorized**: this effort builds the loop, not just decides it.
- Prior receipts: yesterday's hand-run version of this loop (transcript sweep →
  7 behavior fixes, commits 16f6b89d/a5cd0d97/18362f49/2cc52470) is the manual
  baseline the automation replaces. Research corpus:
  `joelclaw-voice/.brain/resources/voice-ux-deep-research-2026-07.svx`.
- Skills: grill-master, herdr-orchestration, session-search, local-convex.

## Decision ledger

- **2026-07-13 — Fast-model A/B ranking:** trial `anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5` first, `openai/gpt-5.4-mini` with reasoning minimized/disabled second, and `openai/gpt-4.1-mini` third; hold Gemini 3.1 Flash Lite until tool-call reliability improves or Exacto routing proves otherwise. Receipt: [fast-model-candidates](./fast-model-candidates.svx). Amended (Joel): grok-4.5 and gpt-5.6-luna|terra:low join the trial cells.
- **2026-07-13 — Honest spoken record:** judge from append-only `conversation_item_added` spoken items, not close-time `session.history` or the rolling `transcriptTail`; interrupted assistant text is LiveKit's synchronized playout transcript. Receipt: [spoken-record-capture](./spoken-record-capture.svx).

- [Define the Auto-Apply Surface](./define-autoapply-surface.svx) — resolved as the autonomy charter `infra/voice-agent/VISION.md`: allowlisted text auto-applies under four mechanical guardrails; persona/config/models gated; quarantine surfaces forbidden; promotion ladder + intelligence escalation (up to pi gpt-5.6-rol:xhigh) defined.

- [Draft the Judge Rubric and Failure Taxonomy](./draft-judge-rubric.svx) — signed: 8 dimensions, 13 tags, N/O-excluded means, four hard-fails, bland public calls cap at 2; calibration = three hand-scored real calls.
- **2026-07-13 — Judge implementation:** host `voice-call-judge` fans out from public and private completion events, dispatches the signed rubric through no-tools pi cheap→escalated tiers, validates quote/hard-fail receipts, writes rich Convex analyses, and exposes a dry-run-first backlog runner. Runtime rollout and corpus mutation remain with steering. Receipt: [build-judge-function](./build-judge-function.svx).

## Not yet specified

- Whether guest/public judge findings ever tune the PRIVATE persona (cross-tier
  learning) or tiers tune independently.
- When the loop earns code-change autonomy.

## Out of scope

- Speech-to-speech model swap — stays behind the workroom brief's latency
  trigger; this loop only feeds it evidence.
- The semantic-memory (libSQL) layer over the public brain — separate effort.
